      transliteration: 'indriyāṇi mano buddhir asyādhiṣṭhānam ucyate\netair vimohayaty eṣa jñānam āvṛtya dehinam',
      translation: 'The senses, mind, and intellect are said to be the dwelling places of desire. Through these, desire deludes the embodied soul by covering its knowledge.',
