      commentary: `The chapter ends with a call to action — but the action is internal. The weapon is not force. The weapon is knowing. "Having known the Self to be beyond the intellect, steady the self by the self." In other words: the part of you that observes desire is not desire. There is something in you that can watch the whole show — the craving, the compulsion, the pull — without being swept away by it. That witnessing awareness is what you anchor in.\n\nYou've been fighting the wrong enemy your entire life. Not the person who challenged you, not the circumstance that frustrated you, not the system that failed you — but the formidable inner force of unexamined desire, which moves you toward choices your clearer self would never make. That is where the real battle is.\n\nThe instruction is precise: know the Self, steady the self by the Self, and from that grounded place — conquer. Not suppress. Conquer. There is a difference. Suppression is white-knuckle restraint. Conquest is freedom — the freedom that comes from being larger than what was trying to rule you.`,
